—and why are you guys also here?

524
00:30:49,569 --> 00:30:53,069
ゼータが来るって聞いたから、アーニャにちょっかいかけてやろうと思って！
We heard Zeta was coming over, and decided to bug ya!

525
00:30:53,069 --> 00:30:54,569
はいはい。
Yes, yes. I see.

526
00:30:55,069 --> 00:30:56,569
もー！つれないなぁ。
Aww, come on!

527
00:30:56,569 --> 00:30:59,069
それはそうと……ゼータ、何か掴めた？
Anyway, Zeta, did you find anything?

528
00:31:00,069 --> 00:31:03,569
もちろん！優秀なシークレットエージェントなので！
Of course! I'm not an elite secret agent for nothing.

529
00:31:04,269 --> 00:31:10,569
イナの描いた似顔絵と大空警察の資料から、被害者の身元を特定できたよ。
Between the portrait from Ina and the files from the Oozora Police, I've been able to positively ID the murder victim.

530
00:31:11,069 --> 00:31:13,569
でも、ちょっと変なんだよね。
But... what I found is weird.

531
00:31:14,069 --> 00:31:15,069
変？
How so?

532
00:31:15,569 --> 00:31:19,569
被害者の履歴を調べたところ、その人物は何百年も前の時代の人だったんだ。
Well, when I investigated their history, I found that they actually lived centuries ago.

533
00:31:20,569 --> 00:31:25,569
でもその人物が、数日前に死体で発見された……話がつながらないよ。
So how they were also somehow murdered just days ago... it doesn't make any sense.

534
00:31:26,069 --> 00:31:29,569
アーニャからもらった情報に間違いがあったとか？
Did you perhaps confuse your information? Or...

535
00:31:30,069 --> 00:31:33,569
なるほど、やっとつながってきた。
Actually, things are finally starting to make sense.

536
00:31:34,069 --> 00:31:34,869
えっ？
Oh?

537
00:31:35,069 --> 00:31:37,569
一人の被害者が、過去と現在で二度死んだことになる。
A victim caught between two times.

538
00:31:38,069 --> 00:31:40,569
誰かが時間と次元をねじ曲げて、そんな状況を作り出した。
One who died in two different ways.

539
00:31:41,069 --> 00:31:46,569
なかなかできることじゃない……
Not many exist who can cause time and dimensions to warp in a way to make that possible...

540
00:31:47,069 --> 00:31:49,569
でも君達なら可能でしょ。
...but you're one of them.

541
00:31:50,869 --> 00:31:52,869
さすがは名探偵。
Well done, detective.

542
00:31:53,569 --> 00:31:54,869
ちょっと時間がかかりすぎかな。
Took you long enough.

543
00:31:55,269 --> 00:31:57,069
危うくネタばらしするとこだった。
I was this close to telling ya the whole thing.

544
00:31:57,269 --> 00:32:00,069
レイネが書いてくれた、この匿名の手紙もいいヒントになったよ。
You helped enough with this "anonymous" letter about the murder.

545
00:32:00,569 --> 00:32:02,569
えっ、バレてた？
O-oh, you figured out that was me?

546
00:32:03,069 --> 00:32:04,869
書き方のクセで分かる。
I recognized your writing style.

547
00:32:05,269 --> 00:32:07,069
待って、どういうこと？
W-wait, I don't get it.

548
00:32:07,269 --> 00:32:09,569
ムーナと被害者にどんな関係があるの？
What does Moona have to do with the victim?

549
00:32:10,069 --> 00:32:14,569
ムーナは、別の時空で殺された遺体を我々がいるこの時空へ移動させたんだ。
She took a murder victim from another space and time, and moved them into our dimension.

550
00:32:15,269 --> 00:32:18,569
ゼータが特定した人物は、この世界線における同じ人物ってこと。
The one you IDed was this universe's version of the same person.

551
00:32:19,269 --> 00:32:23,069
なるほど。でもどうしてそんなことを？
Uh... okay. But then why?

552
00:32:24,269 --> 00:32:29,869
理由も気になるけど、それより確かめたいことがある。
That is an important question, but there's one I want answered even more.

553
00:32:30,569 --> 00:32:33,269
ムーナが……私にあの夢を見せてたの？
Are you... responsible for my dreams?

554
00:32:34,269 --> 00:32:35,569
それは違う。
No.

555
00:32:36,569 --> 00:32:40,569
あなたがあの夢を見ていることを知って、私はあの夢が生まれる根源を調べてみた。
After I learned about your dreams, I used my powers to search for the source of them.

556
00:32:41,269 --> 00:32:44,569
そして見つけたのが、次元の向こう側から声を届けようとする魂。
I found a spirit reaching out from time and dimensions.

557
00:32:45,569 --> 00:32:48,569
私はその魂のために橋渡しを少ししてあげただけ……
All I've done is try to help them by making the bridge a little easier...

558
00:32:49,269 --> 00:32:51,069
私も手伝ったよ！
With my help!

559
00:32:51,269 --> 00:32:52,569
というか、私のアイディア。
I mean, it was my idea...

560
00:32:53,269 --> 00:32:54,869
そう。
True.

561
00:32:55,869 --> 00:33:00,569
ただやり方が悪かったのか、アーニャの見たいものが他の人にも見えちゃったみたい。
Though doing it this way has caused some of what you've been experiencing to leak to other people.

562
00:33:01,269 --> 00:33:04,569
巻き込んだKFPの従業員には後でお詫びしなきゃ……
We're going to have to apologize to the KFP workers...

563
00:33:05,569 --> 00:33:08,569
でもその魂が、どうして私に声を届けようとしてるの？
But why is the spirit reaching out to me of all people?

564
00:33:09,269 --> 00:33:13,269
それは私に訊くことじゃないね。私が話すべきことじゃない。
It wouldn't be right for me to answer those questions. It's not my story to tell.

565
00:33:14,269 --> 00:33:17,569
あの魂に心を開いてあげて。それだけでいい。
Open yourself up to the spirits, and they'll do the rest.

566
00:33:18,569 --> 00:33:20,569
心をもっと開く方法なら知ってるよ！
I got a way to make yourself more open to spirits!

567
00:33:21,269 --> 00:33:22,569
それって歌？
Is it through song?

568
00:33:23,269 --> 00:33:24,569
え？なんで分かったの？
Huh? How'd you know?

569
00:33:25,269 --> 00:33:26,569
まあ、勘かな。
Lucky guess...

570
00:33:55,369 --> 00:33:59,569
想い返していた 思い出の中で泣いていた
I was looking back, crying inside my memories

571
00:34:00,269 --> 00:34:04,569
不確かな夢と 孤独を抱えて笑ってた
With uncertain dreams and loneliness, I was laughing

572
00:34:05,269 --> 00:34:09,569
この痛みも傷もいたいけな瞳も
This pain, these wounds, these innocent eyes too

573
00:34:10,269 --> 00:34:14,569
無に帰してしまいそうな 僕らの日々を
Our days that seem like they'll return to nothingness

574
00:34:16,169 --> 00:34:20,569
誰一人欠けることはない ちぐはぐな
No one is missing, in this mismatched

575
00:34:21,269 --> 00:34:25,569
僕らの思いが 音になって繋ぐ
Our feelings turn into sound and connect us

576
00:34:26,369 --> 00:34:28,069
こだまして
Echoing

577
00:34:28,169 --> 00:34:30,869
忘れないよ 重なり合った日々を
I won't forget the overlapping days

578
00:34:31,169 --> 00:34:35,569
あの日僕らは間違っていなかったんだと知る
Knowing that we weren't wrong that day

579
00:34:36,269 --> 00:34:42,569
葬り去ってしまい込んだ 前線の光探して
Searching for the light on the front line that we buried away

580
00:34:43,269 --> 00:34:45,569
君の声を聞かせて
Let me hear your voice

581
00:34:46,169 --> 00:34:48,569
ここにいるって叫んでくれよ
Shout that you're here

582
00:34:49,169 --> 00:34:53,069
その手を離さないで
Don't let go of that hand

583
00:34:57,269 --> 00:35:01,069
世界に僕だけが取り残されてしまった
I was the only one left behind in the world

584
00:35:00,117 --> 00:35:01,417
まただよな
It's happened again.

585
00:35:01,717 --> 00:35:04,017
暗闇の中で立ち止まり
Stopping in the darkness,

586
00:35:04,217 --> 00:35:05,817
手放してしまう
I end up letting go.

587
00:35:06,617 --> 00:35:09,617
心が通じ合えない孤独感を
The sense of isolation from being unable to connect,

588
00:35:10,017 --> 00:35:12,617
押し殺してしまうなら
if I'm to just suppress it,

589
00:35:12,917 --> 00:35:15,617
一人でいたほうが楽に生きられたかな
maybe it would've been easier to just stay alone.

590
00:35:17,317 --> 00:35:19,117
憧れ
Adoration,

591
00:35:19,317 --> 00:35:21,917
理想に強く惹かれる
strongly attracted to my ideals,

592
00:35:22,417 --> 00:35:24,617
感情が僕らを
these emotions of ours,

593
00:35:24,817 --> 00:35:26,617
引き寄せてしまうのなら
if they are to draw us together,

594
00:35:27,017 --> 00:35:29,917
応えて
then answer me!

595
00:35:37,517 --> 00:35:39,617
凝らして 凝らして
Focus, focus...

596
00:35:39,917 --> 00:35:41,917
まだ終わっちゃいないんだ
It's not over yet,

597
00:35:42,417 --> 00:35:44,917
僕ら 延長戦なんだろう
we're in overtime, aren't we?

598
00:35:45,417 --> 00:35:47,617
この音が途切れるまで
Until this sound fades away completely...

599
00:35:49,617 --> 00:35:53,617
子どもの頃に描いたヒーロー
The hero I pictured as a child,

600
00:35:54,417 --> 00:35:57,617
君の出番が待ってる
is waiting for your turn!

601
00:35:58,417 --> 00:36:00,517
凝らして 忘れないよう
Focus, so I don't forget,

602
00:36:01,017 --> 00:36:03,117
かき鳴らした日々を
the days I strummed away.

603
00:36:03,617 --> 00:36:05,617
あの日 僕らは
On that day, we knew

604
00:36:06,117 --> 00:36:09,117
間違っていなかったんだと知る
that we weren't wrong.

605
00:36:09,717 --> 00:36:12,917
閉ざしてしまいこんだ一閃を
Searching for that flash of light

606
00:36:13,317 --> 00:36:14,617
さがして
I'd locked away deep inside.

607
00:36:15,017 --> 00:36:17,917
君の声を聞かせて
Let me hear your voice,

608
00:36:18,117 --> 00:36:21,617
ここにいるって叫んでくれよ
shout out loud that you are right here!

609
00:36:22,117 --> 00:36:25,617
その手を離さないで
And please, never let go of that hand.

610
00:36:37,117 --> 00:36:39,217
魂に心を開け？
Opening up to the spirit?

611
00:36:39,617 --> 00:36:42,117
簡単に言ってくれる。
That was a tall order.

612
00:36:44,417 --> 00:36:47,917
探偵になる前の彼女の人生において、
In her life before being a detective,

613
00:36:48,517 --> 00:36:52,617
他者に心を開くのは危険な行為だった。
opening up to someone was dangerous.

614
00:36:54,317 --> 00:36:56,617
今でもその本能は変わらない。
That instinct still lingers.

615
00:36:59,517 --> 00:37:02,117
結局何も進展はなかった。
This was getting her nowhere.

616
00:37:02,917 --> 00:37:05,617
謎はまだ残っているが、
She still had questions she needed answered,

617
00:37:05,717 --> 00:37:10,617
彼女はここのところ無理が続いていた。
but maybe she had wound herself up too much.

618
00:37:12,917 --> 00:37:15,617
少し休まなければ。
She needed a break.

619
00:37:24,617 --> 00:37:26,417
Hello everyone!

620
00:37:26,617 --> 00:37:29,117
I'm Hatsune Miku, a virtual idol!

621
00:37:29,617 --> 00:37:32,317
Well, that's what everyone seems to think,

622
00:37:32,517 --> 00:37:34,117
but secretly I'm—

623
00:37:37,117 --> 00:37:39,117
え？ミクちゃん？
Eh? Miku-chan?

624
00:37:40,617 --> 00:37:43,617
アーニャちゃん！一緒に歌おう！
Anya-chan! Let's sing together!

625
00:37:44,417 --> 00:37:46,917
I wake up to a call with my frilly outfit on now.

626
00:37:47,417 --> 00:37:49,617
It's time I open up my eyes and start the day.

627
00:37:49,917 --> 00:37:52,117
I hug the pillow now until happy feelings gone now.

628
00:37:52,417 --> 00:37:54,417
I clumsy trip and now I fall into my bed!

629
00:37:54,917 --> 00:37:57,217
With magical baton and a silver glitter ringtone,

630
00:37:57,417 --> 00:37:59,617
I'll shout the magic words and set the world in place.

631
00:37:59,917 --> 00:38:02,217
Whatever it may cost, there's no reason to stop,

632
00:38:02,417 --> 00:38:04,417
for a world that I cherish and love!

633
00:38:04,817 --> 00:38:07,117
Midst of light, we are here for the fight,

634
00:38:07,217 --> 00:38:09,417
but until the sun sets over,

635
00:38:09,617 --> 00:38:11,917
I can dry up your tears as I wipe them aside,

636
00:38:12,217 --> 00:38:14,417
with a sparkle you'll ever find!

637
00:38:14,717 --> 00:38:16,917
Give my M-A-G-I-C-A-L cure for piece of mind,

638
00:38:17,117 --> 00:38:19,417
I'll always be honest being you every day.

639
00:38:19,517 --> 00:38:21,917
So what if I fall and your tears get from blues,

640
00:38:22,117 --> 00:38:24,417
so happy that I need to clean the cherry blossoms away!

641
00:38:24,517 --> 00:38:26,917
Ha! Fighting through the night of having light the way,

642
00:38:27,117 --> 00:38:29,417
could it all be so hard for me to find the way?

643
00:38:29,517 --> 00:38:31,917
Just smile with enough to make my day,

644
00:38:32,117 --> 00:38:34,417
so I send all the ray!

645
00:38:34,517 --> 00:38:36,917
Catching all the brave and any pain take it all away,

646
00:38:37,017 --> 00:38:39,417
turn up with love, fighting 'til the end!

647
00:38:50,117 --> 00:38:54,617
And now, it's time for the moment you've been waiting for!

648
00:38:55,117 --> 00:38:58,617
One, two, three, ready?

649
00:38:59,617 --> 00:39:02,117
Miku Miku Beam!

650
00:39:08,617 --> 00:39:12,117
On my own, without anyone to know,

651
00:39:12,417 --> 00:39:14,617
how my job is not all rainbows,

652
00:39:14,917 --> 00:39:17,117
but then I think about your smile!

653
00:39:17,417 --> 00:39:19,617
Your words are so lovely!

654
00:39:19,917 --> 00:39:22,217
I'm a magical bright intensely girl,

655
00:39:22,417 --> 00:39:24,617
I will lead you to heal, go on and call my name!

656
00:39:24,917 --> 00:39:27,217
When you find yourself going down a spiral,

657
00:39:27,417 --> 00:39:29,617
I will blow it away, what was your done-of-a-thing-in-my-memory!

658
00:39:29,917 --> 00:39:32,217
Yeah! Fighting through the night of having light the way,

659
00:39:32,417 --> 00:39:34,617
could it all be so hard for me to find the way?

660
00:39:34,917 --> 00:39:37,217
Just smile with enough to make my day,

661
00:39:37,417 --> 00:39:39,617
so I send all the ray!

662
00:39:39,917 --> 00:39:42,217
Catching all the brave and any pain take it all away,

663
00:39:42,417 --> 00:39:44,617
turn up with love, fighting 'til the end!

664
00:40:04,692 --> 00:40:08,092
Wait, so you're saying I've got to be brave?

665
00:40:08,892 --> 00:40:12,792
As long as you can stay happy, I'm okay

666
00:40:13,292 --> 00:40:14,392
I'm not gonna bend, ha!

667
00:40:14,392 --> 00:40:17,592
I can be a cure for kissing your heart away

668
00:40:17,592 --> 00:40:19,492
And I'll play and I'll sing you a whole new way

669
00:40:19,892 --> 00:40:22,092
Your smile is enough to heal all my pain

670
00:40:22,092 --> 00:40:24,792
So M-A-G-I-C-A-L Love Shot!

671
00:40:24,792 --> 00:40:28,092
If you're feeling pain call my name I'll be by your side

672
00:40:28,092 --> 00:40:29,992
Till I see your smile beam bright again

673
00:40:30,492 --> 00:40:31,092
Urya oi! Urya oi!

674
00:40:31,192 --> 00:40:33,892
1-2-3-4 Powerful Mikucchan!

675
00:40:34,692 --> 00:40:35,492
Urya oi! Urya oi!

676
00:40:37,092 --> 00:40:39,592
Cyber Miku-miku go!

677
00:40:40,592 --> 00:40:43,092
あー、眠いよ...
Ah, I'm sleepy...

678
00:41:00,692 --> 00:41:03,592
夢... だった？
Was it... a dream?

679
00:42:51,692 --> 00:42:54,092
知った、救いのない形だった
Understood, it was a form without salvation,

680
00:42:54,092 --> 00:42:58,292
僕の聲は
my voice.

681
00:42:58,592 --> 00:43:01,092
散った、狂いのない
Scattered, the unclouded

682
00:43:01,092 --> 00:43:05,192
赤い血が流れているんだ
red blood is flowing.

683
00:43:05,892 --> 00:43:08,892
ただただ襲い来る影ばかり満ちて
Only shadows are filling, coming to attack me.

684
00:43:08,892 --> 00:43:12,392
抗う言葉も、立ち上がれない夜風
Facing words I can't resist, the wind that won't lift.

685
00:43:12,692 --> 00:43:15,592
赤く光る場所へ、走り出したら
I left for a place that shines red,

686
00:43:15,592 --> 00:43:19,492
ただ膝を抱えている君がいた
and there you were, just holding your knees.

687
00:43:19,492 --> 00:43:22,592
だからENCOUNT、悲劇、決まった、天国へ
That's why an encounter, a tragedy, decided, to heaven.

688
00:43:26,592 --> 00:43:29,692
不甲斐ない瞳きっとあの日、見つめた
Eyes that don't reflect, surely that day, I was staring at them.

689
00:43:29,692 --> 00:43:33,092
君のせいは、早く、早く、早く、早く…
The days that followed, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry...

690
00:43:33,092 --> 00:43:39,992
身を揺らして
Shaking my body.

691
00:43:39,992 --> 00:43:42,592
淡い、淡い、水面の向こうと
Faint, faint, beyond the water's surface...

692
00:44:00,092 --> 00:44:02,092
知った、
Understood,

693
00:44:02,092 --> 00:44:07,092
救いのない熱を持った僕の炎夏
my flaming summer that held a heat without salvation.

694
00:44:07,592 --> 00:44:10,092
散った、
Scattered,

695
00:44:10,092 --> 00:44:14,092
狂いのない貴方の瞳は醜かった
your unclouded eyes were hideous.

696
00:44:14,592 --> 00:44:28,092
酷く、酷く、酷く...
Terribly, terribly, terribly...

697
00:44:41,092 --> 00:44:45,092
ぼう線としてるその顔に
At that dazed face,

698
00:44:45,092 --> 00:44:48,092
触れて
touching it,

699
00:44:48,092 --> 00:44:51,592
見たかった
I wanted to see.

700
00:44:54,892 --> 00:45:00,092
だからENCOUNT、悲劇、決まった、天国へ
That's why an encounter, a tragedy, decided, to heaven.

701
00:45:00,140 --> 00:45:02,140
知った、救いのない形だった僕の聲は
I knew it, it was a hopeless shape, my voice...

702
00:45:02,340 --> 00:45:04,740
奪い合う瞳きっとあの日の
The eyes fighting for one another, surely on that day

703
00:45:04,740 --> 00:45:08,140
移ろった君のせいだ
it was because of you, who changed.

704
00:45:09,240 --> 00:45:14,740
はやくはやくはやくはやくはやくはやくはやくね教えて
Hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, tell me.

705
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:20,440
深い深い秘密の向こうへと
To the other side of deep, deep secrets.

706
00:45:30,140 --> 00:45:32,540
奪い合う瞳きっとあの日の
The eyes fighting for one another, surely on that day

707
00:45:32,540 --> 00:45:35,840
移ろった君のせいだ
it was because of you, who changed.

708
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:43,140
はやくはやくはやくはやくはやくはやくはやくね教えて
Hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, hurry, tell me.

709
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:48,440
淡い淡い秘密の向こうへと
To the other side of faint, faint secrets.

710
00:45:50,640 --> 00:45:53,440
白い光見つめていると
When I stare into the white light,

711
00:45:53,940 --> 00:45:56,640
急な痛みに襲われる
I'm overcome by a sudden pain.

712
00:45:57,340 --> 00:46:01,440
僕は私を保っていられなくなることなど
Things like me becoming unable to maintain my self,

713
00:46:02,140 --> 00:46:06,140
それどこか私の身体が証明している
in fact, my very body is proving it.

714
00:46:07,140 --> 00:46:10,140
初めに、安堵する君が見たい
First, I want to see you relieved.

715
00:46:10,640 --> 00:46:13,640
次に、期待したい
Next, I want to have hope.

716
00:46:34,140 --> 00:46:37,140
この場所で戦いなど起こっていない。
There was no major battle here.

717
00:46:38,140 --> 00:46:40,640
少なくともこの世界線では…。
At least not in this timeline...

718
00:46:42,640 --> 00:46:46,140
だが探偵には分かっていた。
But the detective knows...

719
00:46:46,140 --> 00:46:50,640
彼女が見たものは決して夢ではないことを。
what she saw was no dream.

720
00:46:52,140 --> 00:46:55,940
心の中にはまだ殺戮の匂いが漂っている。
The smell of the carnage still lingers in her mind.

721
00:46:58,140 --> 00:47:03,640
かつての彼女にまとわりついていた。あの匂い。
It's a scent that was, at one time, so familiar to her.

722
00:47:05,140 --> 00:47:08,640
探偵としての生活も今では順調だが、
That stench would still linger on her...

723
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:14,640
そうでなければあの匂いからは離れることができなかったでしょう。
if the detective's life didn't take a turn for the better.

724
00:47:16,940 --> 00:47:22,640
今でも…あの頃の日々がリアルな夢のようにまとわりつく。
Even now... her days felt more like the real dream.

725
00:47:24,140 --> 00:47:26,640
終わるべくして終わったおとぎ話。
A fairytale. Maybe one that deserved to end.

726
00:47:27,640 --> 00:47:30,440
どこまで行っても彼女は、
Because, at the end of the day, she...

727
00:47:30,440 --> 00:47:34,640
生まれ持った本質から逃れることはできない。
can never run away from her nature.

728
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:41,140
それでも今は違う。
But she's not just that anymore.

729
00:47:41,140 --> 00:47:44,340
今の彼女には仲間がいる。
She has friends to thank for that.

730
00:47:44,940 --> 00:47:51,140
それが、別の世界線の彼女とは違う点なのかもしれない。
Maybe that was what separated her from the other version.

731
00:47:53,140 --> 00:47:58,340
もしかしたらあの子は、幸せに生きることのできた世界線があったのだろうかと、
And, maybe... that version of herself just wanted a ray of hope,

732
00:48:02,140 --> 00:48:06,140
そんな一筋の希望を求めていたのだろうか。
to know that there was one timeline where things worked out.

733
00:48:07,140 --> 00:48:15,640
そしてその幸せな世界線というのは、ここではないまた別の世界線のことかもしれない…
Or perhaps this was never about the detective...

734
00:48:17,140 --> 00:48:22,640
考えが頭を巡るものの、答えが出ることはない。
so many thoughts run amok inside her head, but they're forever left unanswered.

735
00:48:24,140 --> 00:48:31,640
何にせよ、探偵は自身の血塗られた過去を忘れることはないでしょう。
Whatever the case, the detective won't forget her bloody past,

736
00:48:32,640 --> 00:48:35,640
しかしまた後戻りするつもりもない。
but she isn't going to revert to it either.

737
00:48:35,640 --> 00:48:42,640
彼女はこれからも仲間とともに進む。
She will continue to move forward with her friends,

738
00:48:44,140 --> 00:48:50,140
望んだ結末を迎えられなかった別の自分達のためにも。
and for all the variants who didn't get their desired ending.

739
00:48:51,140 --> 00:48:53,440
探偵アーニャ・メルフィッサは、
The detective, Anya Melfissa,

740
00:48:54,140 --> 00:48:58,140
明日に向かって生き続ける。
